{title: Send Me to Glory in a Glad Bag}
{artist: John Biggs}
{composer: Written by Don J. Carson, Mim Carson, Steve Mason}

[G]People tell me I ought to save my [C]money
So [D7]that I could be laid away in [G]style
In a walnut box with all the fancy [C]trimmin's
[D7]Vacuum sealed to keep me fresh a [G]while
But Send me to Glory in a [C]glad bag
Don't [D7]waste a fancy coffin on my [G]bones
Just put me out on the curb next [C]Tuesday
Let the [D7]sanitation local bear me [G]home
Sell all my worldly [C]possessions
And [D7]buy yourself a case or two of [G]Pabst
Let the empties be my memorial [C]tombstone
En[D7]grave them with this [G]epitaph
Repeat #2   Send me…
If I should die upon the eve of [C]Christmas
Just [D7]place my baggie by the Christmas [G]tree
When the children they open all their [C]goodies
The [D7]big surprise will be the death of [G]me
Repeat #2   Send me…
But maybe I end up bound for [C]Glory
But [D7]to that other place I would not [G]choose
And if it seems that I'm headed that [C]direction
Then [D7]an oven bag would be the thing to [G]use

Repeat #2 x2  Send me…